---
import SiteLayout from "../../../layouts/SiteLayout.astro";

export const meta = {
  title: "Where To Watch: Streaming Cost Calculator",
  description: "Calculate your monthly streaming subscriptions, track total costs, and evaluate watch-time ROI. Are your platforms actually worth what you pay?",
  category: "tool",
  published: "2026-03-15",
};

const title = meta.title;
const description = meta.description;

const schema = [
  {
    "@context": "https://schema.org",
    "@type": "FAQPage",
    "mainEntity": [
    {
      "@type": "Question",
      "name": "How is the cost per hour of streaming calculated?",
      "acceptedAnswer": {
        "@type": "Answer",
        "text": "The calculator takes the combined total monthly cost of all your active streaming subscriptions and divides it by your estimated total hours of streaming per month. This reveals the true 'cost per hour watched', helping you determine which services provide the most value."
      }
    },
    {
      "@type": "Question",
      "name": "Why should I track my monthly streaming costs?",
      "acceptedAnswer": {
        "@type": "Answer",
        "text": "With the rise of fragmented streaming platforms, it is easy to accumulate 'zombie subscriptions'—services you pay for but rarely use. Tracking costs allows you to identify these unused services, potentially saving hundreds of dollars a year by cancelling underutilized platforms."
      }
    },
    {
      "@type": "Question",
      "name": "What is subscription fatigue?",
      "acceptedAnswer": {
        "@type": "Answer",
        "text": "Subscription fatigue is the frustration consumers experience when forced to subscribe to multiple, increasingly expensive services to access content that used to be aggregated in one place. Evaluating your cost per hour helps combat this fatigue by prioritizing platforms that offer genuine value."
      }
    },
    {
      "@type": "Question",
      "name": "Can I use this tracker for live TV subscriptions like YouTube TV or Sling?",
      "acceptedAnswer": {
        "@type": "Answer",
        "text": "Absolutely. You can add any recurring entertainment cost to the calculator, including cable replacements, premium add-ons, or niche streaming services. Simply add a new service line and input the monthly fee."
      }
    },
    {
      "@type": "Question",
      "name": "What is a good cost per hour for streaming services?",
      "acceptedAnswer": {
        "@type": "Answer",
        "text": "While subjective, a good benchmark is comparing your streaming cost per hour to other forms of entertainment. A movie ticket might cost $15 for 2 hours ($7.50/hr). If your streaming stack costs $0.50 to $1.00 per hour watched, it is generally considered a highly cost-effective form of entertainment."
      }
    }
  ]
  },
  {
    "@context": "https://schema.org",
    "@type": "Article",
    "headline": title,
    "description": description,
    "author": {
      "@type": "Organization",
      "name": "Silicon Based"
    },
    "datePublished": meta.published
  }
];
---

<SiteLayout site="misc" title={title} description={description} canonical="https://photonbuilder.com/misc/where-to-watch-tracker" schema={schema}>
  <div class="page-content">
    <div class="hero">
      <h1>{title}</h1>
      <p class="subtitle">Calculate your monthly streaming stack cost and determine your Return on Investment per hour watched.</p>
    </div>

    <div class="calculator-container">
      <div id="serviceList">
        <!-- Service items injected via JS -->
      </div>

      <button id="addServiceBtn" style="margin-bottom: 2rem;">+ Add Streaming Service</button>

      <div class="input-group" style="margin-top: 1.5rem; padding-top: 1.5rem; border-top: 1px solid var(--border-color);">
        <label for="monthlyHours">Total Estimated Hours Watched (Monthly)</label>
        <div class="input-wrapper">
          <input type="number" id="monthlyHours" min="1" step="1" value="40" placeholder="e.g., 40">
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="result-card">
        <div style="display: grid; grid-template-columns: 1fr 1fr; gap: 1.5rem; text-align: center;">
          <div>
            <div style="color: var(--text-secondary); font-size: 0.95rem; margin-bottom: 0.5rem;">Total Monthly Cost</div>
            <div class="result-value" id="totalCostResult">$0.00</div>
          </div>
          <div>
            <div style="color: var(--text-secondary); font-size: 0.95rem; margin-bottom: 0.5rem;">Cost Per Hour Watched</div>
            <div class="result-value" id="costPerHourResult" style="font-size: 2rem;">$0.00</div>
          </div>
        </div>
        <div style="margin-top: 1.5rem; padding-top: 1.5rem; border-top: 1px solid var(--accent-color); text-align: center;">
           <div style="color: var(--text-secondary); font-size: 0.95rem; margin-bottom: 0.5rem;">Yearly Projection</div>
           <div class="result-value" id="yearlyProjectionResult" style="font-size: 2rem; color: var(--text-primary);">$0.00</div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>

    <div class="explainer">
      <h2>The True Cost of Streaming: Calculating Your Watch-Time ROI</h2>
      <p>The golden age of streaming was defined by convenience and aggregation. A single subscription provided access to a vast, unparalleled library of movies and television. However, the current landscape of digital entertainment is characterized by aggressive fragmentation. Media conglomerates have siloed their content, launching proprietary platforms and steadily increasing monthly fees. This <strong>Where To Watch Tracker</strong> is designed to help you quantify your digital entertainment expenses and calculate the real Return on Investment (ROI) of your streaming habits.</p>

      <h3>The Methodology Behind the Calculator</h3>
      <p>Determining the value of a streaming service is highly subjective. A $20/month subscription might be a massive waste of money for someone who watches one movie a month, but an incredible bargain for a household streaming four hours of content a day. To objectify this value, our calculator uses a straightforward but illuminating metric: <strong>Cost Per Hour Watched</strong>.</p>

      <p>The calculator aggregates your monthly recurring revenue (MRR) outflow dedicated to streaming services. It then divides this cumulative financial burden by your estimated monthly viewing hours.</p>

      <div class="formula-box">
        Total Monthly Cost = &Sigma; (Individual Service Subscription Fees)<br><br>
        Cost Per Hour = Total Monthly Cost / Total Monthly Hours Watched<br><br>
        Yearly Projection = Total Monthly Cost &times; 12
      </div>

      <h3>Combating "Zombie Subscriptions" and Subscription Fatigue</h3>
      <p>One of the primary business models of modern streaming platforms relies on user inertia. Services actively bank on the fact that users will sign up to watch a specific, exclusive show (like a blockbuster fantasy series or a live sports event) and subsequently forget to cancel the subscription once the show concludes.</p>

      <p>These forgotten accounts are often referred to as "zombie subscriptions." By inputting your entire streaming stack into the calculator and observing the Yearly Projection, the financial impact of user inertia becomes starkly apparent. A seemingly harmless $12/month service translates to $144 a year. If you only watch two hours of content on that specific platform a month, your cost per hour for that specific service balloons to $6.00/hr—approaching the cost of a physical movie ticket.</p>

      <h3>Streaming vs. Traditional Cable: Evaluating the Shift</h3>
      <p>For years, the rallying cry of "cord-cutting" was driven by the desire to escape bloated, expensive cable packages. However, as consumers are forced to subscribe to Netflix, Hulu, Max, Disney+, Prime Video, and Apple TV+ simultaneously to maintain access to popular culture, the combined cost of these "micro-subscriptions" is rapidly approaching, and in some cases exceeding, the cost of legacy cable.</p>

      <p>This calculator empowers you to audit your digital life. By forcing you to list out your services and quantify your watch time, you can strategically cycle your subscriptions. Instead of maintaining year-round access to every platform, savvy consumers are increasingly adopting a rotation strategy: subscribing to one platform for a month, binge-watching its exclusive content, cancelling, and moving to the next. This drastically lowers the Total Monthly Cost while keeping the Total Hours Watched relatively stable, optimizing your Cost Per Hour.</p>

      <p>If you are looking to optimize your daily commute as well as your entertainment budget, consider using our <a href="/bus-tracker">Bus Tracker Calculator</a> to estimate your transit times.</p>
    </div>

    <section class="faq-section">
      <h2>Frequently Asked Questions</h2>

      <details>
        <summary>How is the cost per hour of streaming calculated?</summary>
        <p>The calculator takes the combined total monthly cost of all your active streaming subscriptions and divides it by your estimated total hours of streaming per month. This reveals the true 'cost per hour watched', helping you determine which services provide the most value.</p>
      </details>

      <details>
        <summary>Why should I track my monthly streaming costs?</summary>
        <p>With the rise of fragmented streaming platforms, it is easy to accumulate 'zombie subscriptions'—services you pay for but rarely use. Tracking costs allows you to identify these unused services, potentially saving hundreds of dollars a year by cancelling underutilized platforms.</p>
      </details>

      <details>
        <summary>What is subscription fatigue?</summary>
        <p>Subscription fatigue is the frustration consumers experience when forced to subscribe to multiple, increasingly expensive services to access content that used to be aggregated in one place. Evaluating your cost per hour helps combat this fatigue by prioritizing platforms that offer genuine value.</p>
      </details>

      <details>
        <summary>Can I use this tracker for live TV subscriptions like YouTube TV or Sling?</summary>
        <p>Absolutely. You can add any recurring entertainment cost to the calculator, including cable replacements, premium add-ons, or niche streaming services. Simply add a new service line and input the monthly fee.</p>
      </details>

      <details>
        <summary>What is a good cost per hour for streaming services?</summary>
        <p>While subjective, a good benchmark is comparing your streaming cost per hour to other forms of entertainment. A movie ticket might cost $15 for 2 hours ($7.50/hr). If your streaming stack costs $0.50 to $1.00 per hour watched, it is generally considered a highly cost-effective form of entertainment.</p>
      </details>
    </section>

  </div>

  <script is:inline>
    document.addEventListener('DOMContentLoaded', () => {
      const serviceList = document.getElementById('serviceList');
      const addServiceBtn = document.getElementById('addServiceBtn');
      const monthlyHoursInput = document.getElementById('monthlyHours');

      const totalCostResult = document.getElementById('totalCostResult');
      const costPerHourResult = document.getElementById('costPerHourResult');
      const yearlyProjectionResult = document.getElementById('yearlyProjectionResult');

      const defaultServices = [
        { name: 'Netflix (Standard)', cost: 15.49 },
        { name: 'Hulu (No Ads)', cost: 17.99 },
        { name: 'Max (Ad-Free)', cost: 15.99 }
      ];

      function createServiceItem(name = '', cost = '') {
        const div = document.createElement('div');
        div.className = 'service-item';

        const nameInput = document.createElement('input');
        nameInput.type = 'text';
        nameInput.placeholder = 'Service Name (e.g. Netflix)';
        nameInput.value = name;

        const costInput = document.createElement('input');
        costInput.type = 'number';
        costInput.min = '0';
        costInput.step = '0.01';
        costInput.placeholder = 'Monthly Cost ($)';
        costInput.value = cost;
        costInput.className = 'cost-input';

        const removeBtn = document.createElement('button');
        removeBtn.className = 'remove-btn';
        removeBtn.textContent = 'X';
        removeBtn.onclick = () => {
          div.remove();
          calculate();
        };

        nameInput.addEventListener('input', calculate);
        costInput.addEventListener('input', calculate);

        div.appendChild(nameInput);
        div.appendChild(costInput);
        div.appendChild(removeBtn);

        return div;
      }

      function calculate() {
        let totalCost = 0;

        const costInputs = document.querySelectorAll('.cost-input');
        costInputs.forEach(input => {
          const val = parseFloat(input.value);
          if (!isNaN(val) && val >= 0) {
            totalCost += val;
          }
        });

        const monthlyHours = parseFloat(monthlyHoursInput.value);
        let costPerHour = 0;

        if (!isNaN(monthlyHours) && monthlyHours > 0) {
          costPerHour = totalCost / monthlyHours;
        }

        const yearlyProjection = totalCost * 12;

        totalCostResult.textContent = '$' + totalCost.toFixed(2);

        if (isNaN(monthlyHours) || monthlyHours <= 0) {
           costPerHourResult.textContent = '--';
        } else {
           costPerHourResult.textContent = '$' + costPerHour.toFixed(2) + '/hr';
        }

        yearlyProjectionResult.textContent = '$' + yearlyProjection.toFixed(2);
      }

      // Initialize default list
      defaultServices.forEach(service => {
        serviceList.appendChild(createServiceItem(service.name, service.cost));
      });

      addServiceBtn.addEventListener('click', () => {
        serviceList.appendChild(createServiceItem());
        calculate();
      });

      monthlyHoursInput.addEventListener('input', calculate);

      // Initial calculation
      calculate();
    });
  </script>

  <style is:inline>
    .page-content { max-width: 900px; margin: 0 auto; padding: 2rem 1.5rem; }
    .hero { text-align: center; padding: 3rem 0 2rem; }
    .hero h1 { font-size: 2.2rem; font-weight: 800; margin-bottom: 0.5rem; }
    .subtitle { color: var(--text-secondary); font-size: 1.1rem; }
    .calculator-container { background: var(--card-bg); border: 1px solid var(--border-color); border-radius: 12px; padding: 2rem; margin: 2rem 0; }
    .service-item { display: flex; gap: 1rem; margin-bottom: 1rem; align-items: center; }
    .service-item input { flex: 1; }
    .remove-btn { background: #ef4444; padding: 0.75rem 1rem; }
    input, select { background: var(--bg-color); color: var(--text-primary); border: 1px solid var(--border-color); padding: 0.75rem 1rem; border-radius: 8px; width: 100%; font-size: 1rem; }
    input:focus, select:focus { outline: none; border-color: var(--accent-color); box-shadow: 0 0 0 3px color-mix(in srgb, var(--accent-color) 20%, transparent); }
    button { background: var(--accent-color); color: white; border: none; padding: 0.75rem 2rem; border-radius: 8px; font-weight: 600; cursor: pointer; font-size: 1rem; }
    button:hover { opacity: 0.9; }
    .result-card { background: color-mix(in srgb, var(--accent-color) 10%, transparent); border: 1px solid var(--accent-color); border-radius: 12px; padding: 1.5rem; margin: 1.5rem 0; text-align: center; }
    .result-value { font-size: 2.5rem; font-weight: 800; color: var(--accent-color); }
    .faq-section { margin-top: 3rem; }
    .faq-section h2 { font-size: 1.75rem; margin-bottom: 1.5rem; color: var(--accent-color); }
    .faq-section details { margin: 1rem 0; padding: 1rem; background: var(--card-bg); border-radius: 8px; border: 1px solid var(--border-color); }
    .faq-section summary { font-weight: 600; cursor: pointer; font-size: 1.1rem; color: var(--text-primary); margin-bottom: 0.5rem; }
    .faq-section p { margin-top: 0.5rem; color: var(--text-secondary); line-height: 1.6; }
    .explainer { margin-top: 3rem; line-height: 1.7; color: var(--text-secondary); }
    .explainer h2 { font-size: 1.75rem; margin-top: 2rem; margin-bottom: 1rem; color: var(--accent-color); }
    .explainer h3 { font-size: 1.3rem; margin-top: 1.5rem; margin-bottom: 0.75rem; color: var(--text-primary); }
    .explainer p { margin-bottom: 1.2rem; }
    .explainer ul, .explainer ol { margin-bottom: 1.2rem; padding-left: 1.5rem; }
    .explainer li { margin-bottom: 0.5rem; }
    .formula-box { background: var(--bg-color); padding: 1rem; border-radius: 8px; border-left: 4px solid var(--accent-color); margin: 1rem 0; font-family: monospace; }
  </style>
</SiteLayout>
